                        "version": 0,
                        "content": "A client who has rheumatoid arthritis has begun treatment with anakinra and has received the first injection. What finding would indicate that the primary health care provider (PHCP) needs to be notified and that the medication would be discontinued?",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "80db17ea97ed8fdcd1b6b9666390fca1",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Applying 应用",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nLeukocytosis and a slight temperature elevation can indicate an infection in a client on a biological response modifier. These findings warrant PHCP notification and possible discontinuation of the medication. Irritation and erythema are common and can be decreased by rotating the injection sites. Arthritic medications often are given with other medications, such as a tumor necrosis factor inhibitor. Arthritic symptoms often do not lessen early in the treatment.\n\nTest-Taking Strategy:\nFocus on the subject, medication complication of anakinra. Common occurrences during the first few weeks of treatment include injection site reactions (irritation and erythema) and no relief of arthritic symptoms, so these options can be eliminated. Using combinations of medications often is necessary for the best therapeutic response, so concurrent therapy with tumor necrosis factor inhibitor can also be eliminated. The correct option could indicate signs of infection.",
                        "id": "70a27739c8d94bc4a8b3fd68d096bcbf",
                        "mark": "0",
                        "collectionState": "0"
                    },
                    {
                        "optionList": [
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "31f2aa19f4b34cc88063c737f9b0dff3",
                                "content": "Nausea"
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "2b196987243a4fa0a13260949c480cf1",
                                "content": "Diarrhea"
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "516ca6a04f2e428c85e0262e60efd412",
                                "content": "Loss of appetite"
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "1",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "f68c8950e8c3439bb4cbfce9670cf222",
                                "content": "Metallic taste in the mouth"
                            }
                        ],
                        "extJson": {
                            "optionList": [
                                {
                                    "isRight": "0",
                                    "userAnswer": "",
                                    "isSelected": "0",
                                    "id": "31f2aa19f4b34cc88063c737f9b0dff3",
