                        "content": "Auranofin has been prescribed for a client with rheumatoid arthritis. The nurse provides instructions to the client about the medication and tells the client to notify the primary health care provider if which occurs?",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "80db17ea97ed8fdcd1b6b9666390fca1",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Applying 应用",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nAuranofin is a gold preparation that is given orally rather than by injection. Gastrointestinal (GI) reactions including diarrhea, abdominal pain, nausea, and loss of appetite are common early in therapy but usually subside in the first 3 months. Early signs and symptoms of toxic reactions include a rash, purple blotches, pruritus, mouth lesions, and a metallic taste in the mouth. Signs and symptoms of toxic reactions are reported to the primary health care provider (PHCP).\n\nTest-Taking Strategy:\nNote the words notify the primary health care provider. Recalling that auranofin is a gold preparation will direct you to the correct option. Also, the options of nausea, diarrhea, and loss of appetite are comparable or alike in that they all are GI signs and symptoms.",
                        "id": "800e4818d8f3436bb522baba0571bfdc",
                        "mark": "0",
                        "collectionState": "0"
                    },
                    {
                        "optionList": [
                            {
                                "isRight": "1",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "cb8539e4f00e48d2b2000549d3c46511",
                                "content": "\"Do you have any joint pain?\""
