                        "content": "The nurse reviews the medication history of a client and notes that the client is taking leflunomide. During assessment of the client, the nurse would ask which question to determine the effectiveness of this medication.",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "a0f7d178f7b728b8bba7ef20ddeca62d",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Evaluating 评价",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nLeflunomide is an immunomodulatory agent and has an anti-inflammatory action. The medication provides symptomatic relief of rheumatoid arthritis. Diarrhea can occur as a side effect of the medication. The questions in the remaining options are unrelated to the action, use, or effectiveness of the medication.\n\nTest-Taking Strategy:\nNote the strategic word, effectiveness, and focus on the subject, determining medication effectiveness. It is necessary to know the medication classification of leflunomide. Recalling that leflunomide has anti-inflammatory effects will direct you to option 1.",
