                        "type": "0",
                        "version": 0,
                        "content": "A client has been on treatment for rheumatoid arthritis for 3 weeks. During the administration of etanercept, which is most important for the nurse to assess?",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "80db17ea97ed8fdcd1b6b9666390fca1",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Applying 应用",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nInfection and pancytopenia are adverse effects of etanercept. Laboratory studies are performed before and during medication treatment. The appearance of abnormal white blood cell counts and abnormal platelet counts can alert the nurse to a potentially life-threatening infection. Injection site itching is a common occurrence following administration. A metallic taste and loss of appetite are not common adverse effects of this medication.\n\nTest-Taking Strategy:\nNote the strategic words, most important. Option 4 can be eliminated, because these are not common adverse effects. In early treatment, residual fatigue and joint pain may still be apparent. For the remaining options, the correct option monitors for a hematological disorder, which could indicate a reason for discontinuing this medication and should be reported.",
                        "id": "eae3c14bfd1e4bc4a10e459ac86b2947",
                        "mark": "0",
                        "collectionState": "0"
                    },
                    {
                        "optionList": [
                            {
                                "isRight": "1",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "69ab2496af7647779fb21aa7cd35fe96",
                                "content": "Control of symptoms during periods of emotional stress"
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "1",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "78af384811cc417c9b0f8cf8165a494a",
                                "content": "Normal white blood cell, platelet, and neutrophil counts"
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "1",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "e887c6583f4845039f08dd5000e9257e",
                                "content": "Radiological findings that show no progression of joint degeneration"
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "1",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "58cc7ec785b84b70af96eb09c5e0480c",
                                "content": "An increased range of motion in the affected joints 3 months into therapy"
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "a7f86cee3c7b4acf8c11f069493c3e4d",
                                "content": "Inflammation and irritation at the injection site 3 days after the injection is given"
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "a0da3162ada14f5d83fc19fb3137f184",
                                "content": "A low-grade temperature on rising in the morning that remains throughout the day"
                            }
                        ],
                        "extJson": {
                            "optionList": [
                                {
                                    "isRight": "1",
                                    "userAnswer": "",
                                    "isSelected": "0",
                                    "id": "69ab2496af7647779fb21aa7cd35fe96",
                                    "content": "Control of symptoms during periods of emotional stress"
                                },
                                {
                                    "isRight": "1",
                                    "userAnswer": "",
                                    "isSelected": "0",
                                    "id": "78af384811cc417c9b0f8cf8165a494a",
                                    "content": "Normal white blood cell, platelet, and neutrophil counts"
                                },
                                {
                                    "isRight": "1",
                                    "userAnswer": "",
                                    "isSelected": "0",
                                    "id": "e887c6583f4845039f08dd5000e9257e",
                                    "content": "Radiological findings that show no progression of joint degeneration"
                                },
                                {
                                    "isRight": "1",
                                    "userAnswer": "",
                                    "isSelected": "0",
                                    "id": "58cc7ec785b84b70af96eb09c5e0480c",
                                    "content": "An increased range of motion in the affected joints 3 months into therapy"
                                },
                                {
                                    "isRight": "0",
                                    "userAnswer": "",
                                    "isSelected": "0",
                                    "id": "a7f86cee3c7b4acf8c11f069493c3e4d",
                                    "content": "Inflammation and irritation at the injection site 3 days after the injection is given"
                                },
